        <type>double</type>
        <definition>double form_factor_broad_peak</definition>
        <argsstring>(double q, void *f_ctx)</argsstring>
        <name>form_factor_broad_peak</name>
        <param>
          <type>double</type>
          <declname>q</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>void *</type>
          <declname>f_ctx</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Computes the broad_peak form factor. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>q</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>value at which to compute the transform </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>f_ctx</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>pointer to struct containing inputs for form factor. f_ctx must contain a pointer to an array of parameters. The parameters, which appear in the formula <formula id="1">\[ I(Q) = \frac{I_0}{\left(1 + (|q - q_0| \xi)^m \right)^p} \]</formula> need to be in the following order:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><formula id="2">$ I_0 $</formula> : Forward scattering intensity (e.g. 1e5)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><formula id="0">$ \xi $</formula> : Correlation length (e.g. 1000)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><formula id="3">$ q_0 $</formula>: Peak position, related to d-spacing: <formula id="4">$ q_0 = \frac{2\pi}{d} $</formula> (e.g. 0.01)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><formula id="5">$ m $</formula> : Exponent <formula id="6">$m$</formula> (e.g. 2)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><formula id="7">$ p $</formula> : Exponent <formula id="8">$p$</formula> (e.g. 2) </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
